@page
@model WinCCOAOutsideInfoRepo.Pages.DebuggingModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Troubleshooting and Debugging in WinCC OA";
}

<div class="container">
    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <h3>Error Handling</h3>
    <p>Error handling is crucial in WinCC OA project development. Learn to identify and manage different error types, utilize try-catch blocks, and log errors for analysis.</p>

    <h3>Log Analysis</h3>
    <p>Understand the importance of log files in diagnosing issues. Explore log file locations, log levels, and the Log Viewer tool for effective log analysis.</p>

    <h3>Debugging Tools</h3>
    <p>Discover WinCC OA's debugging tools, including the integrated debugger, breakpoints, Watch, and Locals windows. Learn to use them for efficient code inspection and correction.</p>

    <h3>Common Debugging Scenarios</h3>
    <p>Explore real-world debugging scenarios, such as data point issues, script logic errors, communication problems, and visualization debugging. Gain insights into how to approach and resolve these issues.</p>

    <h3>Best Practices</h3>
    <p>Adopt best practices for effective troubleshooting and debugging. Learn to isolate issues, test hypotheses, and document debugging steps for future reference.</p>

    <h3>Real-Life Examples</h3>
    <p>Review real-life debugging examples with code snippets, log entries, and step-by-step procedures. Practice your debugging skills with hands-on examples.</p>
</div>


